reference: This is becoming less of an issue as lens manufacturers achieve higher standards in lens production.
translation: As the manufacturers of contact lenses reach higher standards in production, the problem becomes less of a concern.

source: Cela a permis aux zooms de produire des images d'une qualité comparable à celle obtenue par des objectifs à longueur focale fixe.
reference: This has allowed zoom lenses to produce pictures of a quality comparable to that achieved by lenses with fixed focal length.
translation: This allowed the zoom lenses to produce comparable images to those obtained by fixed focal length lenses.

source: Un autre inconvénient des objectifs zooms est que l’ouverture (la vitesse) maximale de l’objectif est généralement plus faible.
reference: Another disadvantage of zoom lenses is that the maximum aperture (the speed) of the lens is usually lower.
translation: Another disadvantage of zoom lenses is that the maximum aperture (the speed) is usually lower.

source: Cela rend les objectifs zoom peu coûteux difficiles à utiliser dans des conditions de faible luminosité sans flash.
reference: This makes inexpensive zoom lenses hard to use in low-light conditions without a flash.
translation: This makes it difficult to use the zoom lenses in low-light conditions without flash.

source: L'un des problèmes les plus courants lors de la conversion d'un film en format DVD est le surbalayage.
reference: One of the most common problems when trying to convert a movie to DVD format is the overscan.
translation: One of the most common problems when converting a film to DVD format is the overheating.

source: La plupart des télévisions sont fabriquées de manière à plaire au grand public.
reference: Most televisions are made in a way to please the general public.
translation: Most television sets are designed to please the general public.

source: Pour cette raison, tout ce que vous visionnez sur télévision a les bords coupés en haut, en bas et sur les côtés.
reference: For that reason, everything you see on the TV had the borders cut, top, bottom and sides.
translation: This is why, all you see on television has the top, bottom and sides cut off.

source: Il faut donc veiller à ce que l'image couvre tout l'écran. C'est ce qu'on appelle l'overscan.
reference: This is made to ensure that the image covers the whole screen. That is called overscan.
translation: So, we must ensure that the image covers the entire screen. This is called overscan.

source: Malheureusement, lorsque vous réalisez un DVD, ses bords seront probablement coupés aussi, et si la vidéo comportait des sous-titres trop proches du bas de l'écran, ils n'apparaîtront pas.
reference: Unfortunately, when you make a DVD, it's borders will most likely be cut too, and if the video had subtitles too close to the bottom, they won't be fully shown.
translation: Unfortunately, when you make a DVD, the edges of the disc may be cut, and if the video contained subtitles that were too close to the bottom of the screen, they may not appear.

source: Le château médiéval traditionnel a longtemps stimulé l'imagination, évoquant des images de joutes, de banquets et de chevalerie arthurienne.
reference: The traditional medieval castle has long inspired the imagination, conjuring up images of jousts, banquets and Arthurian chivalry.
translation: The medieval castle has long been a popular tourist attraction, evoking images of joutes, banquets and knightly adventures.

source: Même au milieu de ruines millénaires, il est facile de se rappeler les bruits et les odeurs de batailles lointaines, d'entendre presque le cliquetis des sabots sur les pavés et de sentir la peur monter des fosses du donjon.
reference: Even standing amidst thousand year-old ruins it is easy to bring to mind the sounds and smells of battles long gone, to almost hear the clatter of hooves on the cobbles and to smell the fear rising from the dungeon pits.
translation: Even in the ruins of centuries, it is easy to remember the sounds and smells of distant battles, to hear almost the clatter of the feet on the pavement, and to feel the fear rising from the tombs.

source: Mais notre imagination est-elle basée sur la réalité ? Pourquoi a-t-on construit des châteaux en premier lieu ? Comment ont-ils été conçus et construits ?
reference: But is our imagination based on reality? Why were castles built in the first place? How were they designed and built?
translation: But our imagination is based on reality? Why did we build castles first? How were they designed and built?

source: Typique de l'époque, le château de Kirby Muxloe relève plus d'une maison fortifiée que d'un véritable château.
reference: Typical for the period, Kirby Muxloe Castle is more of a fortified house than a true castle.
translation: This is typical of the time, the Kirby Muxloe castle is more of a fortified castle than a real castle.

source: Ses baies fenêtres vitrées et ses minces parois n'auraient pas pu résister longtemps à un assaut acharné.
reference: Its large glazed windows and thin walls would not have been able to resist a determined attack for long.
translation: His windows and narrow walls would not have resisted long against a fierce assault.

source: Dans les années 1480, lorsque sa construction fut lancée par Lord Hastings, le pays était relativement paisible et la défense n’était nécessaire que contre de petites bandes de maraudeurs itinérants.
reference: In the 1480s, when its construction was begun by Lord Hastings, the country was relatively peaceful and defense was only required against small bands of roving marauders.
translation: In the 1480s, when Lord Hastings started the construction of the castle, the country was relatively quiet and the defence was only needed against small bands of marauders.

source: L'équilibre des pouvoirs était un système dans lequel les nations européennes cherchaient à maintenir la souveraineté nationale de tous les États européens.
reference: The balance of power was a system in which European nations sought to maintain the national sovereignty of all European states.
translation: The balance of power was a system in which European nations sought to maintain the national sovereignty of all European states.

source: L'idée était que toutes les nations européennes empêchent une nation de devenir puissante, c'est pourquoi les gouvernements nationaux changeaient souvent d'alliances afin de maintenir l'équilibre.
reference: The concept was that all European nations had to seek to prevent one nation from becoming powerful, and thus national governments often changed their alliances in order to maintain the balance.
translation: The idea was that all European nations prevented a nation from becoming powerful, so that nations changed their alliances frequently to maintain the balance.

source: La Guerre de Succession d’Espagne marqua la Première Guerre dont l’issue principale fut l’équilibre des pouvoirs.
reference: The War of Spanish Succession marked the first war whose central issue was the balance of power.
translation: The Spanish Succession marked the first major war of the First World War. The outcome was the balance of power.

source: Cela a marqué un changement important, car les puissances européennes ne pourraient plus utiliser le prétexte des guerres de religion. Ainsi, la guerre de Trente Ans serait la dernière guerre à être qualifiée de guerre de religion.
reference: This marked an important change, as European powers would no longer have the pretext of being religious wars. Thus, the Thirty Years' War would be the last war to be labeled a religious war.
translation: This marked a significant change, as European powers could no longer use the pretext of religious wars. Thus, the last religious war would be the last to be called a religious war.

source: Le temple d'Artémis à Ephèse a été détruit le 21 juillet 356 avant J.-C. lors d'un incendie criminel commis par Herostratus.
reference: The temple of Artemis at Ephesus was destroyed on July 21, 356 BCE in an act of arson committed by Herostratus.
translation: Ephesus temple was destroyed on 21 July 356 BC by Herostratus.

source: D'après l'histoire, sa motivation était la célébrité à tout prix. Les Ephésiens, indignés, annoncent que le nom d'Herostratus ne sera jamais enregistré.
reference: According to the story, his motivation was fame at any cost. The Ephesians, outraged, announced that Herostratus' name never be recorded.
translation: According to the story, his motivation was to be famous. Ephesians, indignant, announce that the name of Herostratus will never be recorded.

source: L'historien grec Strabo mentionna ce nom plus tard et c'est ainsi qu'il nous est parvenu. Le temple fut détruit la même nuit qui vit la naissance d'Alexandre le Grand.
reference: The Greek historian Strabo later noted the name, which is how we know today. The temple was destroyed on the same night that Alexander the Great was born.
translation: The Greek historian Strabo mentioned this name later and so it is known today. The temple was destroyed the same night that Alexander the Great was born.

source: Alexandre, en tant que roi, offrit de payer pour reconstruire le temple, mais son offre fut déclinée. Plus tard, après la mort d’Alexandre, le temple fut reconstruit en 323 avant notre ère.
reference: Alexander, as king, offered to pay to rebuild the temple, but his offer was denied. Later, after Alexander died, the temple was rebuilt in 323 BCE.
translation: Alexander, as king, offered to pay for the temple's reconstruction, but his offer was declined. Later, after the death of Alexander, the temple was rebuilt in 323 BC.

source: Vérifiez que votre main soit détendue le plus possible lorsque vous jouez chaque note  correctement. Essayez également de ne pas faire de mouvements inutiles avec vos doigts.
reference: Make sure your hand is as relaxed as possible while still hitting all the notes correctly - also try not to make much extraneous motion with your fingers.
translation: Check that your hand is relaxed the most possible while playing each note correctly. Try not to make unnecessary movements with your fingers.

source: Vous vous fatigueriez moins de cette façon. N'oubliez pas qu'il n'est pas nécessaire de trop insister sur les touches pour qu'elles résonnent plus fort. C'est le cas sur le piano.
reference: This way, you will tire yourself out as little as possible. Remember there's no need to hit the keys with a lot of force for extra volume like on the piano.
translation: This way, you would not feel tired. Don't forget that it is not necessary to overdo the keys to make them sound louder. This is the case on the piano.

source: Avec l'accordéon, pour produire plus de volume, actionnez le soufflet en augmentant la pression ou la vitesse des mouvements.
reference: On the accordion, to get extra volume, you use the bellows with more pressure or speed.
translation: With the accordion, to produce more volume, increase the pressure or speed of the movements.

source: Le mysticisme est la recherche de la communion, du lien avec une divinité ou d'un dieu. C'est la pleine conscience d'une vérité spirituelle.
reference: Mysticism is the pursuit of communion with, identity with, or conscious awareness of an ultimate reality, divinity, spiritual truth, or God.
translation: Mysticism is the search for communion, the union with a deity or a god. It is the full awareness of a spiritual truth.

source: Le croyant recherche une expérience directe, une intuition ou une révélation de la réalité divine/de la divinité ou des dieux.
reference: The believer seeks a direct experience, intuition, or insight into divine reality/the deity or dieties.
translation: The believer seeks a direct experience, intuition, or revelation of the divine reality or divine or gods.

source: Les adeptes poursuivent certains modes de vie, ou des pratiques qui visent à nourrir ces expériences.
reference: Followers pursue certain ways of living, or practices that are intended to nurture those experiences.
translation: The followers pursue certain lifestyles or practices that nourish those experiences.

source: Le mysticisme peut être distingué des autres formes de culte et de croyance à caractère religieux par son accent sur l'expérience personnelle directe d'un état unique de conscience, notamment dans le cas d'une personnalité paisible, intuitive, heureuse, voire extatique.
reference: Mysticism can be distinguished from other forms of religious belief and worship by its emphasis on the direct personal experience of a unique state of consciousness, particularly those of a peaceful, insightful, blissful, or even ecstatic character.
translation: The mysticism can be distinguished from other forms of religion and belief by its emphasis on personal experience of a unique state of consciousness, including in the case of a peaceful, intuitive, happy, or extatic personality.

source: Le sikhisme est une religion du sous-continent indien, née au XVe siècle dans la région du Pendjab, à la suite d’un schisme au sein de la tradition hindouiste.
reference: Sikhism is a religion from the Indian sub-continent. It originated in the Punjab region during the 15th century from a sectarian split within the Hindu tradition.
translation: Sikhism is a subcontinent Indian religion, which was born in the 15th century in the Punjab region, following a schism within the Hindu religion.

source: Les sikhs considèrent que leur foi est une religion distincte de l'hindouisme, bien qu'ils reconnaissent ses racines et ses traditions hindoues.
reference: Sikhs consider their faith to be a separate religion from Hinduism though they acknowledge its Hindu roots and traditions.
translation: Sikhs consider their faith to be a separate religion from Hinduism, but acknowledge its roots and traditions of Hinduism.

source: Les sikhs appellent leur religion Gurmat, ce qui signifie « voie du gourou » en pendjabi. Le gourou est un aspect fondamental de toutes les religions indiennes, mais dans le sikhisme, il a pris une importance qui forme le noyau des croyances sikhes.
reference: Sikhs call their religion Gurmat, which is Punjabi for "way of the guru". The guru is a fundamental aspect of all Indian religions but in Sikhism has taken on an importance that forms the core of Sikh beliefs.
translation: Sikhism calls its religion Gurmat, which means "path of the guru" in Punjabi. Gurmat is a fundamental aspect of all Indian religions, but in Sikhism, it has taken on a greater significance.

source: La religion a été fondée au XVe siècle par le gourou Nanak (1469-1539). Neuf autres gourous se sont succédés.
reference: The religion was founded in the 15th century by Guru Nanak (1469–1539). There followed in succession a further nine gurus.
translation: The religion was founded in the 15th century by the gourou Nanak (1469-1539). Nine other gourous followed.

source: Cependant, en juin 1956, les promesses de Khrouchtchev ont été mises à l'épreuve lorsque les émeutes en Pologne, où les travailleurs protestaient contre les pénuries alimentaires et les réductions de salaires, se sont transformées en une protestation générale contre le communisme.
reference: However, in June 1956, Krushchev's promises were put to the test when riots in Poland, where workers were protesting against food shortages and wage cuts, turned into a general protest against Communism.
translation: However, in June 1956, the promises of Khrouchtchev were tested when the riots in Poland, where the workers protested against food shortages and wage cuts, turned into a general protest against communism.

source: Bien qu’en fin de compte, Kroutchev ait envoyé des chars pour rétablir l’ordre, il a cédé à certaines exigences économiques et a accepté de nommer le populaire Wladyslaw Gomulka comme nouveau premier ministre.
reference: Although in the end, Krushchev sent in tanks to restore order, he did give way to some economic demands and agreed to appoint the popular Wladyslaw Gomulka as the new prime minister.
translation: In fact, Kroutchev sent tanks to restore order, but he agreed to some economic demands and accepted the popular Wladyslaw Gomulka as his new prime minister.

source: La civilisation de la vallée de l'Indus est une civilisation de l'âge de bronze du sous-continent indien du nord-ouest, qui englobe la plus grande partie du Pakistan actuel et certaines régions du nord-ouest de l'Inde et du nord-est de l'Afghanistan.
reference: The Indus Valley Civilization was a Bronze Age civilisation in the northwest Indian subcontinent encompassing most of modern-day Pakistan and some regions in northwest India and northeast Afghanistan.
translation: The civilization of the Indus Valley is a bronze age civilization in the Indian subcontinent of the northwest, which covers the entire Pakistan and some of the northwest of India and the northeast of Afghanistan.

source: Cette civilisation a prospéré dans les bassins de l’Indus, d’où son nom.
reference: The civilisation flourished in the basins of the Indus River wherefore it derives its name.
translation: This civilization flourished in the Indus valleys, and its name is derived from it.

source: Certains universitaires soutiennent néanmoins qu'étant donné que cette civilisation était également présente dans les bassins du fleuve Sarasvati aujourd'hui asséché, elle devrait justement être appelée la civilisation de l'Indus-Sarasvati, alors que certains la nomment civilisation Harappan d'après Harappa, le premier de ses sites à avoir été mis au jour, dans les années 1920.
reference: Although some scholars speculate that since the civilisation also existed in the basins of the now dried up Sarasvati River, it should be aptly called the Indus-Sarasvati Civilization, while some call it the Harappan Civilization after Harappa, the first of its sites to be excavated in the 1920s.
translation: Some scholars support the idea that the Indus-Sarasvati civilization was also present in the present-day Sarasvati River basin, and that it should be called the Indus-Sarasvati civilization, while others call it Harappan civilization from Harappa, the first site discovered in the 1920s.

source: La nature militariste de l’empire romain a contribué au développement des progrès de la médecine.
reference: The militaristic nature of the Roman empire aided in the development of medical advances.
translation: Roman imperialism contributed to the development of medicine.

source: L'empereur Auguste entreprit de recruter des médecins et forma même le premier corps médical romain chargé de soigner les victimes des batailles.
reference: Doctors began to be recruited by Emperor Augustus and even formed the first Roman Medical Corps for use in the aftermath of battles.
translation: Augustus began to recruit doctors and formed the first medical corps in Rome to treat the victims of battles.

source: Les chirurgiens connaissaient divers sédatifs comme la morphine, ce produit tirée des graines de pavot ainsi que la scopolamine, extraite de graines de jusquiame noire.
reference: Surgeons had knowledge of various sedatives including morphine from extracts of poppy seeds and scopolamine from herbane seeds.
translation: The surgeons knew various sedatives as morphine, which is derived from the seeds of poppy and scopolamine, which is derived from the seeds of blackberry.

source: Ils devinrent des experts de l’amputation en sauvant des patients de la gangrène, ainsi qu’en matière de pinces à ligature et de pinces artérielles servant à juguler le flux sanguin.
reference: They became proficient at amputation to save patients from gangrene as well as tourniquets and arterial clamps to stem blood flow.
translation: They became experts in amputations by saving patients from gangrene, and in the use of arterioplasty and arteriovenous cannulas for juggling blood flow.

source: À travers les siècles, l'empire romain a grandement œuvré dans le domaine de la médecine, et est à l'origine de la plupart des connaissances que nous possédons aujourd'hui.
reference: Over multiple centuries, the Roman empire led to great gains in the field of medicine and formed much of the knowledge we know today.
translation: Through the centuries, the Roman empire has greatly contributed to the field of medicine, and has been the origin of most of the knowledge we have today.

source: L'origami Pureland est un origami avec la contrainte qu'un seul pli peut être fait à la fois, les plis plus complexes comme les plis inversés ne sont pas autorisés, et tous les plis ont des emplacements simples.
reference: Pureland origami is origami with the restriction that only one fold may be done at a time, more complex folds like reverse folds are not allowed, and all folds have straightforward locations.
translation: Pureland Origami is a Pureland origami with the constraint that only one fold can be made at a time, complex foldings such as inverted folds are not allowed, and all folds have simple locations.

source: Il a été développé par John Smith dans les années 1970 pour aider les personnes inexpérimentées ou ayant des capacités motrices limitées.
reference: It was developed by John Smith in the 1970s to help inexperienced folders or those with limited motor skills.
translation: It was developed by John Smith in the 1970s to help inexperienced or limited motorists.

source: Les enfants prennent très tôt conscience de la notion de race et des stéréotypes raciaux, et ces stéréotypes ont une incidence sur le comportement.
reference: Children develop an awareness of race and racial stereotypes quite young and these racial stereotypes affect behavior.
translation: Children are very early aware of race and racial stereotypes, and these stereotypes have an impact on behavior.

source: Par exemple, les enfants qui s'identifient à une minorité raciale perçue habituellement comme peu performante à l'école ont tendance à échouer à l'école dès qu'ils découvrent le stéréotype associé à leur race.
reference: For instance, children who identify with a racial minority that is stereotyped as not doing well in school tend to not do well in school once they learn about the stereotype associated with their race.
translation: For example, children who identify as a minority group who are perceived as less performant at school tend to fail at school when they discover the stereotype associated with their race.

source: MySpace est le troisième site Internet le plus populaire utilisé aux États-Unis et compte actuellement 54 millions de profils.
reference: MySpace is the third most popular website used in the United States and has 54 million profiles currently.
translation: MySpace is the third most popular website in the United States and currently has 54 million profiles.

source: Ces sites Web ont suscité un grand intéret, surtout le volet éducation.
reference: These websites have gotten a lot of attention, especially in the education setting.
translation: These websites have generated a lot of interest, especially the education section.

source: Ces sites ont des côtés bénéfiques, y compris de pouvoir facilement mettre en place des types de page qui comprennent des blogs, des vidéos, des photos, et d'autres fonctionnalités.
reference: There are positive aspects to these websites, which include, being able to easily setup a class page which can include blogs, videos, photos, and other features.
translation: These sites have benefits, including the ability to easily create blogs, videos, photos, and other features.

source: Cette page est accessible facilement à partir d'une seule adresse Web, ce qui la rend facile à mémoriser et à écrire pour les étudiants qui ne savent pas utiliser un clavier et qui ont des problèmes d'orthographe.
reference: This page can easily be accessed by providing just one web address, which makes it easy to remember and easy to type in for students who may have trouble using the keyboard or with spelling.
translation: This page is accessible from a single URL, which makes it easy to remember and write for students who don't know how to use a keyboard and have trouble with spelling.

source: Elle peut être personnalisée afin d'en faciliter la lecture, et l'on peut y mettre autant ou aussi peu de couleur que l'on souhaite.
reference: It can be customized to make it easy to read and also with as much or little color as desired.
translation: The text can be customized to make it easier to read, and we can add as much or as little color as we want.

source: Le trouble déficitaire de l'attention « est un syndrome neurologique dont les trois symptômes caractéristiques sont l'impulsivité, la difficulté à se concentrer et l'hyperactivité (ou excès d'énergie) ».
reference: Attention Deficit Disorder "is a neurological syndrome whose classic defining triad of symptoms including impulsivity, distractibility, and hyperactivity or excess energy".
translation: The ADHD syndrome is a neurological condition characterized by three symptoms that are impulsivity, difficulty concentrating, and hyperactivity (or excess energy).

source: Ce n'est pas un handicap d'apprentissage. C'est un trouble de l'apprentissage qui affecte 3 à 5 % des enfants et concerne près de 2 millions d'enfants américains.
reference: It is not a learning disability, it is a learning disorder; it "affects 3 to 5 percent of all children, perhaps as many as 2 million American children".
translation: This is not a learning disability. It is a learning disability affecting 3 to 5 percent of children and affecting 2 million American children.

source: Les enfants atteints de TDA ont du mal à se concentrer sur des choses telles que les travaux scolaires, mais ils peuvent se concentrer sur ce qu'ils aiment faire, comme jouer à des jeux ou regarder leurs dessins animés préférés ou écrire des phrases sans ponctuation.
reference: Children with ADD have a hard time focusing on things like school work, but they can concentrate on things they enjoy doing like playing games or watching their favorite cartoons or writing sentences without punctuation.
translation: Children with TDA have trouble focusing on school work, but they can concentrate on what they enjoy doing, such as playing games or watching their favorite shows or writing sentences without punctuation.

source: Ce sont des enfants qui ont tendance à avoir des difficultés importantes, car ils « adoptent des comportements à risque, se battent et défient l'autorité » afin de stimuler leur cerveau, puisque celui-ci ne peut être stimulé par des activités normales.
reference: These children tend to get into a lot of trouble, because they "engage in risky behaviors, get into fights, and challenge authority" in order to stimulate their brain, since their brain can not be stimulated by normal methods.
translation: These are children who tend to have major difficulties, because they "engage in risky behaviors, fight and defy authority to stimulate their brain."

source: Le TDA affecte les relations avec les autres enfants, qui ne peuvent pas comprendre pourquoi les malades agissent de la sorte, pourquoi ils épellent comme ils le font, ou pourquoi leur niveau de maturité est différent.
reference: ADD affects relationships with other peers because other children can not understand why they act the way that they do or why they spell they way they do or that their maturity level is different.
translation: The TDA affects relationships with other children, who cannot understand why the patients do this, why they spell as they do, or why their maturity level is different.

source: Comme la capacité à acquérir la connaissance et à apprendre a changé d'une certaine façon telle que mentionnée ci-dessus, le rythme de base auquel la connaissance s'acquérait a changé.
reference: As the ability to obtain knowledge and to learn changed in such a way as mentioned above the base rate at which knowledge was obtained changed.
translation: As the ability to acquire knowledge and learn has changed, the basic rate at which knowledge was acquired has changed.

source: La manière de récupérer l'information était différente. Il n'y avait plus de pression sur la mémoire individuelle, mais la capacité à se souvenir d'un texte devenait plus importante.
reference: The approach to obtaining information was different. No longer did pressure reside within individual recall, but the ability to recall text became more of a focus.
translation: The way to retrieve information was different. Memory was no longer a matter of individual memory, but memory of a text became more important.

source: En somme, la Renaissance a été à l'origine d'un changement majeur dans la façon d'envisager l'apprentissage et la diffusion des connaissances.
reference: In essence, the Renaissance made a significant change in the approach to learning and the dissemination of knowledge.
translation: In sum, the Renaissance has been the birthplace of a major change in the way we think about learning and dissemination of knowledge.

source: Les hominidés n'utilisent plus leurs mains pour marcher, porter des charges lourdes ou se balancer d'une branche à l'autre d'un arbre comme les autres primates.
reference: Unlike other primates, hominids no longer use their hands in locomotion or bearing weight or swinging through the trees.
translation: The hominid species no longer use their hands to walk, carry heavy loads or swing from branch to branch of a tree as other primates.

source: La main et le pied du chimpanzé sont similaires en taille et en longueur, ce qui reflète l'utilisation de la main pour porter le poids dans la locomotion sur les articulations.
reference: The chimpanzee's hand and foot are similar in size and length, reflecting the hand's use for bearing weight in knuckle walking.
translation: The chimpanzé's hand and foot are similar in size and length, which reflects the use of the hand to carry weight in locomotion.

source: La main de l'homme est plus courte que son pied, avec des phalanges plus rigides.
reference: The human hand is shorter than the foot, with straighter phalanges.
translation: The man's hand is shorter than his foot, with more rigid phalanges.

source: Les os de la main d'un fossile, vieux de deux à trois millions d'années, révèlent la mutation qu'a subit la fonction de la main lors du passage de la locomotion à la manipulation.
reference: Fossil hand bones two million to three million years old reveal this shift in specialization of the hand from locomotion to manipulation.
translation: Fossils from the hand of a two to three million-year-old dinosaur reveal the mutation that has occurred in the hand's function during locomotion to manipulation.

source: Certaines personnes pensent que faire de nombreux rêves lucides provoqués artificiellement et assez souvent peut être très épuisant.
reference: Some people believe that experiencing many artificially induced lucid dreams often enough can be very exhausting.
translation: Some people think that having many lucid dreams caused artificially and often can be very exhausting.

source: La raison principale de ce phénomène est le résultat des rêves lucides qui allongent la durée entre les états de sommeil paradoxal.
reference: The main reason for this phenomenon is the result of the lucid dreams expanding the length of time between REM states.
translation: The main reason for this phenomenon is the result of lucid dreams that prolong the sleep cycle.

source: Avec moins de sommeil paradoxal par nuit, cet état dans lequel vous profitez d'un vrai sommeil réparateur devient suffisamment rare pour devenir problématique.
reference: With fewer REMs per night, this state in which you experience actual sleep and your body recovers becomes infrequent enough to become a problem.
translation: With less sleep deprivation per night, this state of having a real sleepy night becomes problematic enough to become a problem.

source: C’est tout aussi épuisant que de se réveiller toutes les vingt ou trente minutes et de regarder la télévision.
reference: This is just as exhausting as if you were to wake up every twenty or thirty minutes and watch TV.
translation: It's as exhausting as waking up every twenty or thirty minutes and watching TV.

source: L’effet dépend de la fréquence à laquelle votre cerveau tente de rêver lucidement par nuit.
reference: The effect is dependent on how often your brain attempts to lucidly dream per night.
translation: The effect depends on how often your brain tries to dream lucidly in the night.

source: Les choses prirent une mauvaise tournure pour les Italiens en Afrique du Nord quasiment dès le début. Une semaine après la déclaration de guerre de l’Italie le 10 juin 1940, les 11e hussards britanniques s’emparèrent du Fort Capuzzo en Libye.
reference: Things did not go well for the Italians in North Africa almost from the start. Within a week of Italy's declaration of war on June 10, 1940, the British 11th Hussars had seized Fort Capuzzo in Libya.
translation: The Italian forces in Africa of North were almost immediately attacked by the 11e Hussars. On 10 June 1940, the British 11th Hussars took the fort of Capuzzo in Libya.

source: Dans une embuscade à l'est de Bardia, les Britanniques ont capturé l'ingénieur en chef de la dixième armée italienne, le général Lastucci.
reference: In an ambush east of Bardia, the British captured the Italian Tenth Army's Engineer-in-Chief, General Lastucci.
translation: In the east of Bardia, the British captured the Italian general in charge of the 10th army.

source: Le 28 juin, le maréchal Italo Balbo, gouverneur général de Libye et successeur potentiel de Mussolini, fut tué par un tir ami alors qu'il atterrissait à Tobrouk.
reference: On June 28, Marshal Italo Balbo, the Governor-General of Libya and apparent heir to Mussolini, was killed by friendly fire while landing in Tobruk.
translation: On August 28, Italo Balbo, the governor general of Libya and the eventual successor to Mussolini, was killed by an enemy fire while landing in Tobruk.

source: Le sport moderne qu'est l'escrime se pratique à de nombreux niveaux, depuis les étudiants qui en font l'apprentissage à l'université jusqu'aux compétitions professionnelles et olympiques.
reference: The modern sport of fencing is played at many levels, from students learning at a university to professional and Olympic competition.
translation: Modern sport is practiced at many levels, from the student who learns it at university to professional and Olympic competitions.

source: Ce sport se pratique principalement dans un format de duel, un escrimeur se battant contre un autre.
reference: The sport is primarily played in a duel format, one fencer dueling another.
translation: This sport is mainly played in a duel format, where the contestant is battling against another.

source: Le golf est un jeu dans lequel les joueurs utilisent des clubs pour frapper des balles et les envoyer dans des trous.
reference: Golf is a game in which players use clubs to hit balls into holes.
translation: Golf is a game in which players use clubs to hit balls and send them into holes.

source: Une partie se joue ordinairement en dix-huit trous : les joueurs commencent en règle générale par le premier trou du parcours et terminent par le dix-huitième.
reference: Eighteen holes are played during a regular round, with players usually starting on the first hole on the course and finishing on the eighteenth.
translation: The game is played in 18 holes: the players begin in the first hole of the course and finish in the 18th hole.

source: Le joueur qui encaisse le moins de coups, ou de swings avec le club, pour terminer le parcours gagne.
reference: The player who takes the fewest strokes, or swings of the club, to complete the course wins.
translation: The player who receives the least number of hits or swings with the club, to finish the course wins.

source: Le jeu se joue sur l'herbe, et le gazon qui entoure le trou est coupé plus court et appelé le « green ».
reference: The game is played on grass, and the grass around the hole is mown shorter and called the green.
translation: The game is played on the grass, and the grass around the hole is cut shorter and called the "green".

source: Le type de tourisme le plus répandu est peut-être celui que la plupart des gens associent au voyage : Le tourisme récréatif.
reference: Perhaps the most common type of tourism is what most people associate with traveling: Recreation tourism.
translation: The most common type of tourism is probably the one most people associate with travel: recreational tourism.

source: C'est le moment où les gens se rendent dans un endroit, complètement différent de ce qu'il voit au quotidien, pour se détendre et prendre du bon temps.
reference: This is when people go to a place that is very different from their regular day-to-day life to relax and have fun.
translation: This is the time when people go to a place, completely different from what they see everyday, to relax and take good time.

source: Les plages, les parcs à thème et les terrains de camping sont souvent les lieux les plus fréquentés par les touristes de loisirs.
reference: Beaches, theme parks and camp grounds are often the most common places frequented by recreational tourists.
translation: The beaches, theme parks and camping grounds are often the most popular tourist destinations.

source: Si l'objectif de la visite d'un lieu particulier est de connaître son histoire et sa culture, ce type de tourisme s'appelle alors tourisme culturel.
reference: If the objective of one’s visit to a particular place is to get to know its history and culture then this type of tourism is known as cultural tourism.
translation: If the purpose of a visit is to learn about the history and culture of a place, this type of tourism is called cultural tourism.

source: Les touristes peuvent visiter différents sites d'un pays donné ou choisir de se concentrer sur une seule région.
reference: Tourists may visit different landmarks of a particular country or they may simply opt to focus on just one area.
translation: Tourists can visit different places from a country or choose to focus on a single region.

source: Les colonisateurs, ayant repéré cette activité, avaient également appelé des renforts.
reference: The Colonists, seeing this activity, had also called for reinforcements.
translation: The colonists also called in reinforcements.

source: Les troupes renforçant les positions avancées comprenaient les 1er et 3e régiments du New Hampshire de 200 hommes, sous les ordres des colonels John Stark et James Reed (tous deux devenus généraux par la suite).
reference: Troops reinforcing the forward positions included the 1st and 3rd New Hampshire regiments of 200 men, under Colonels John Stark and James Reed (both later became generals).
translation: The reinforcing troops consisted of the 1st and 3rd New Hampshire Regiment of 200 men under the command of the colonels John Stark and James Reed (both later promoted to generals).

source: Les hommes de Stark ont pris position le long de la clôture, à l'extrémité nord de la position du colon.
reference: Stark's men took positions along the fence on the north end of the Colonist's position.
translation: The men of Stark were positioned along the fence, at the northern end of the position of the colon.

source: Lorsque la marée basse a creusé un écart le long de la Mystic River dans le nord-est de la presqu'île, on a rapidement agrandi la barrière par un muret de pierre au nord se terminant au bord de l'eau sur une petite plage.
reference: When low tide opened a gap along the Mystic River along the northeast of the peninsula, they quickly extended the fence with a short stone wall to the north ending at the water's edge on a small beach.
translation: When the low tide dug a small gap along the Mystic River in the northeast of the island, we quickly built a stone wall on the north shore of the river on a small beach.

source: Gridley ou Stark a placé un pieu à environ 30 mètres devant la clôture et a ordonné que personne ne tire avant que les habitués ne la franchissent.
reference: Gridley or Stark placed a stake about 100 feet (30 m) in front of the fence and ordered that no one fire until the regulars passed it.
translation: Gridley or Stark placed a stake about 30 feet away from the fence and ordered that no one should shoot until the regulars had crossed.

source: Le plan américain reposait sur le lancement d'attaques coordonnées depuis trois directions différentes.
reference: The American plan relied on launching coordinated attacks from three different directions.
translation: The plan of the American was to launch coordinated attacks from three different directions.

source: Le général John Cadwalder lance une attaque de diversion contre la garnison britannique de Bordentown, afin de bloquer tout renfort.
reference: General John Cadwalder would launch a diversionary attack against the British garrison at Bordentown, in order to block off any reinforcements.
translation: General John Cadwalder launches a diversionary attack against British garrison at Bordentown, to block any reinforcements.

source: Le général James Ewing fera traverser la rivière à 700 miliciens à Trenton Ferry, s'emparera du pont sur l'Assunpink Creek et empêchera les troupes ennemies de s'échapper.
reference: General James Ewing would take 700 militia across the river at Trenton Ferry, seize the bridge over the Assunpink Creek and prevent any enemy troops from escaping.
translation: General James Ewing will cross the river at 700 militia at Trenton Ferry, take the bridge over the Assunpink Creek and prevent the enemy from escaping.

source: La principale force d'assaut, composée de 2 400 hommes, franchit la rivière à neuf miles au nord de Trenton, puis se divisa en deux groupes, l'un sous Greene et l'autre sous Sullivan, afin de lancer une attaque avant l'aube.
reference: The main assault force of 2,400 men would cross the river nine miles north of Trenton, and then split into two groups, one under Greene and one under Sullivan, in order to launch a pre-dawn attack.
translation: The main assault force, consisting of 2,400 men, crossed the river at nine miles north of Trenton, and divided into two groups, one under Greene and the other under Sullivan, to launch an attack before dawn.

source: Avec le passage du 400 mètres au 800 mètres, la vitesse devient beaucoup moins importante et l’endurance devient une nécessité absolue.
reference: With the change from the quarter to the half mile run, speed becomes of much less importance and endurance becomes an absolute necessity.
translation: With the passage of the 400 m to the 800 m, the speed becomes much less important and the need for endurance becomes a necessity.

source: Bien sûr, un excellent coureur de demi-fond, un homme capable de battre un record de deux minutes doit posséder une bonne pointe de vitesse, mais surtout une endurance parfaitement cultivée.
reference: Of course a first-class half-miler, a man who can beat two minutes, must be possessed of a fair amount of speed, but endurance must be cultivated at all hazards.
translation: Yes, a very good runner of half-figures, a man who can beat a record of two minutes, must have a very good speed, but also a very good endurance.

source: Un peu de cross-country en hiver, combiné à un travail en salle pour la partie supérieure du corps, est la meilleure préparation pour la saison de course.
reference: Some cross country running during the winter, combined with gymnasium work for the upper part of the body, is the best preparation for the running season.
translation: A little cross-country in winter combined with a workout in the upper body for the upper body is the best preparation for the race season.

source: De bonnes pratiques nutritionnelles ne suffisent pas à elles seules à garantir des performances d'élite, mais elles peuvent avoir un impact significatif sur le bien-être général des jeunes athlètes.
reference: Proper nutritional practices alone cannot generate elite performances, but they can significantly affect young athletes' overall wellness.
translation: Nutrition practices alone do not guarantee elite performance, but they can have a significant impact on the general well-being of young athletes.

source: Le maintien d'un bon équilibre énergétique, une hydratation adéquate et régulière et de bonnes connaissances concernant les différents aspects liés aux suppléments nutritionnels peuvent aider les athlètes à améliorer leurs performances et à se faire encore davantage plaisir dans le cadre de leur pratique sportive.
reference: Maintaining a healthy energy balance, practicing effective hydration habits, and understanding the various aspects of supplementation practices can help athletes improve their performance and increase their enjoyment of the sport.
translation: The maintenance of a good energy balance, proper hydration and regular intake of nutritional supplements can help athletes improve their performance and enjoy their sport more.

source: Le demi-fond est un sport relativement peu coûteux. L'idée qu'il nécessiterait un équipement basique est aussi fausse que la plupart des mythes qui entourent ce sport.
reference: Middle distance running is a relatively inexpensive sport; however, there are many misconceptions regarding the few pieces of equipment required to participate.
translation: Half-figures is a relatively inexpensive sport. The idea that it would require basic equipment is also false as much as most myths surrounding this sport.

source: Les produits peuvent être achetés si le besoin se fait sentir, mais la plupart n'auront que peu ou aucune incidence réelle sur la performance de l'athlète.
reference: Products can be purchased as needed, but most will have little or no real impact on performance.
translation: Products can be purchased if the need arises, but most will have little or no real impact on the athlete's performance.

source: Les athlètes peuvent avoir le sentiment qu'ils préfèrent un produit même si celui-ci n'apporte aucun réel avantage.
reference: Athletes may feel that they prefer a product even when it provides no real benefits.
translation: Athletes may feel that they prefer a product even if it does not offer any real benefit.

source: L'atome peut être considéré comme étant l'une des unités qui constitue toute matière.
reference: The atom can be considered to be one of the fundamental building blocks of all matter.
translation: The atom can be considered as one of the units that constitute all matter.

source: Il s’agit d’une entité très complexe qui consiste, selon un modèle de Bohr simplifié, en un noyau central orbité par des électrons, un peu comme les planètes en orbite autour du soleil — cf. illustration 1.1.
reference: Its a very complex entity which consists, according to a simplified Bohr model, of a central nucleus orbited by electrons, somewhat similar to planets orbiting the sun - see Figure 1.1.
translation: This is a very complex entity that is, according to Bohr's simplified model, composed of a central core orbiting by electrons, like the planets around the sun. This is illustrated in Figure 1.1.

source: Le noyau est constitué de deux particules — des neutrons et des protons.
reference: The nucleus consists of two particles - neutrons and protons.
translation: The core is made up of two particles — neutrons and protons.

source: Les protons ont une charge électrique positive tandis que les neutrons n'ont pas de charge. Les électrons ont une charge électrique négative.
reference: Protons have a positive electric charge while neutrons have no charge. The electrons have a negative electric charge.
translation: The protons have a positive charge while the neutrons have no charge. The electrons have a negative charge.

source: Avant d'examiner la victime, assurez-votre sécurité en inspectant les lieux.
reference: To Check the victim, you must first survey the scene to ensure your safety.
translation: Before examining the victim, assure yourself of your safety by inspecting the scene.

source: Vous devez remarquer la position de la victime lorsque vous vous approchez d'elle et tout signal d'alerte manifeste.
reference: You need to notice the victim's position as you approach him or her and any automatic red flags.
translation: You must notice the victim's position when you approach her and any obvious warning sign.

source: Si vous vous blessez en essayant d'aider, vous ne ferez qu'empirer les choses.
reference: If you get hurt trying to help, you may only serve to make matters worse.
translation: If you try to help, you will only worsen the situation.

source: L'étude a révélé que la dépression, la peur et le catastrophisme étaient à l'origine de la relation entre la douleur et le handicap chez les personnes souffrant de douleurs au bas du dos.
reference: The study found that depression, fear and catastrophising mediated the relationship between pain and disability in lower back pain sufferers.
translation: The study revealed that depression, fear and catastrophism were the primary cause of the relationship between pain and disability in people with back pain.

source: Seuls les effets de la catastrophe, et non la dépression et la peur, étaient conditionnés par des séances hebdomadaires régulières et structurées d'AP.
reference: Only the effects of catastrophizing, not depression and fear was conditional of regular weekly structured PA sessions.
translation: The only conditioned effect of the disaster was depression and fear, not the effects of the disaster itself.

source: Ceux qui participent à une activité régulière ont besoin de plus de soutien en termes de perception négative de la douleur, en distinguant les différences entre la douleur chronique et la sensation d'inconfort et le mouvement physique normal.
reference: Those participating in regular activity required more support in terms of negative perception of pain distinguishing the differences of chronic pain and discomfort feel from normal physical movement.
translation: Those who participate in regular activity need more support in terms of negative perception of pain, distinguishing chronic pain from discomfort and normal movement.

source: La vision, ou la capacité de voir, dépend du système visuel, des organes sensoriels ou des yeux.
reference: Vision, or the ability to see depends on visual system sensory organs or eyes.
translation: Vision depends on the visual system, the sensory organs, or the eyes.

source: Les anatomies oculaires varient. Elles sont classées par ordre de complexité en fonction des exigences de l'organisme.
reference: There are many different constructions of eyes, ranging in complexity depending on the requirements of the organism.
translation: The anatomy of the eye varies. It is classified according to the requirements of the organism.

source: Les diverses constructions ont des capacités différentes, sont sensibles à des longueurs d’onde distinctes et ont des degrés d’acuité différents. Elles nécessitent également des traitements distincts pour l’interprétation des données reçues et les nombres qu’il leur faut pour fonctionner de manière optimale diffèrent aussi.
reference: The different constructions have different capabilities, are sensitive to different wave-lengths and have differing degrees of acuity, also they require different processing to make sense of the input and different numbers to work optimally.
translation: The various constructions have different capacities, are sensitive to different wavelengths, and have different degrees of acuity. They also require different processing to interpret the data received and the numbers they need to operate optimally.

source: Une population est l'ensemble des organismes d'une espèce particulière dans une zone géographique donnée.
reference: A population is the collection of organisms of a particular species within a given geographic area.
translation: A population is the set of organisms of a particular species in a given geographic area.

source: Lorsque tous les individus d'une population sont identiques en ce qui concerne un trait phénotypique particulier, on dit qu'ils sont monomorphes.
reference: When all individuals in a population are identical with regard to a particular phenotypic trait they are known as monomorphic.
translation: When all individuals of a population are identical in a particular trait, we say they are monomorphic.

source: Lorsque les individus présentent plusieurs variantes d'un trait particulier, ils sont polymorphes.
reference: When the individuals show several variants of a particular trait they are polymorphic.
translation: When individuals present multiple variants of a trait, they are polymorphic.

source: Les colonies de fourmis de l’armée marchent et nichent également dans différentes phases.
reference: Army ant colonies march and nest in different phases as well.
translation: The army ant colonies march and nest in different phases.

source: Durant la période nomade, les fourmis légionnaires marchent la nuit et s'arrêtent pour camper le jour.
reference: In the nomadic phase, army ants march at night and stop to camp during the day.
translation: During nomadic life, the soldiers march the night and rest the day.

source: La colonie entame une phase nomade lorsque la nourriture disponible a diminué. Pendant cette phase, la colonie construit des nids temporaires qui sont changés tous les jours.
reference: The colony begins a nomadic phase when available food has decreased. During this phase, the colony makes temporary nests that are changed everyday.
translation: The colony begins a nomadic phase when the food available has decreased. During this phase, the colony builds temporary nests every day.

source: Chacun de ces raids ou chacune de ces razzias dure environ 17 jours.
reference: Each of these nomadic rampages or marches lasts for approximately 17 days.
translation: Each raid or each raid lasts about 17 days.

source: Qu’est-ce qu’une cellule ? Le mot « cellule » vient du mot latin « cella », qui signifie « petite pièce », et a été inventé par un microscopiste qui observait la structure du liège.
reference: What is a cell? The word cell comes from the Latin word "cella", meaning "small room", and it was first coined by a microscopist observing the structure of cork.
translation: What is a cell? The word "cell" comes from the Latin "cella", which means "petite room", and was invented by a microscopist who observed the structure of liège.

source: La cellule est l'unité de base de tous les êtres vivants, et tous les organismes sont composés d'une ou plusieurs cellules.
reference: The cell is the basic unit of all living things, and all organisms are composed of one or more cells.
translation: Cell is the basic unit of all living things, and all organisms are composed of one or more cells.

source: Dans l'étude du vivant, les cellules sont tellement essentielles qu'on les considère bien souvent comme les fondamentaux de la vie.
reference: Cells are so basic and critical to the study of life, in fact, that they are often referred to as "the building blocks of life".
translation: In the study of life, the cells are so essential that they are often considered to be the fundamental elements of life.

source: Le système nerveux maintient l’homéostasie en envoyant des impulsions nerveuses à travers le corps pour maintenir le flux sanguin aussi bien en marche que non perturbé.
reference: The Nervous System maintains homeostasis by sending nerve impulses through out the body to keep the flow of blood going as well as undisturbed.
translation: The nervous system maintains homeostasis by sending impulses through the body to maintain blood flow in both motion and unperturbed.

source: Ces impulsions nerveuses peuvent être envoyées très rapidement dans tout le corps, ce qui contribue à le protéger contre toute menace potentielle.
reference: These nerve impulses can be sent so quickly throughout the body which helps keep the body safe from any potential threat.
translation: These nerve impulses can be sent very quickly throughout the body, which helps to protect it from any potential threat.

source: Les tornades frappent une petite zone par rapport à d’autres tempêtes violentes, mais elles peuvent tout détruire sur leur passage.
reference: Tornadoes strike a small area compared to other violent storms, but they can destroy everything in their path.
translation: Tornadoes strike a small area in relation to other violent storms, but they can destroy everything on their way.

source: Les tornades déracinent les arbres, arrachent les planches des bâtiments et projettent les voitures dans le ciel. Les deux pour cent de tornades les plus violentes durent plus de trois heures.
reference: Tornadoes uproot trees, rip boards from buildings, and fling cars up into the sky. The most violent two percent of tornadoes last more than three hours.
translation: The tornadoes destroy the trees, tear up the buildings and throw cars into the sky. The two percent of the most violent tornadoes last for three hours.

source: Ces tempêtes géantes comporte des vents soufflant jusqu'à 480 km/h (133 m/s ou 300 mph).
reference: These monster storms have winds up to 480 km/h (133 m/s; 300 mph).
translation: These giant storms have winds reaching up to 480 km/h (133 m/s or 300 mph).

source: L'homme fabrique et utilise des lentilles pour l'agrandissement depuis des milliers et des milliers d'années.
reference: Humans have been making and using lenses for magnification for thousands and thousands of years.
translation: The man uses lenses to enlarge things for millions and millions of years.

source: Toutefois, les premiers vrais télescopes furent fabriqués en Europe à la fin du XVIe siècle.
reference: However, the first true telescopes were made in Europe in the late 16th century.
translation: However, the first true telescopes were made in Europe in the 16th century.

source: Ces télescopes utilisaient une combinaison de deux lentilles afin que les objets distants paraissent à la fois plus gros et plus proches.
reference: These telescopes used a combination of two lenses to make distant objects appear both nearer and larger.
translation: These telescopes used two lenses to make objects appear to be larger and closer together.

source: L’avidité et l’égoïsme feront toujours partie de nous. Il est naturel dans un rapport de coopération de gagner plus et rapidement, en agissant avec égoïsme, lorsque la majorité est avantagée.
reference: Greed and selfishness will always be with us and it is the nature of cooperation that when the majority benefit there will always be more to gain in the short term by acting selfishly
translation: The selfishness and envy will always be part of us. It is natural in a cooperative relationship to gain more quickly and more easily, when the majority is favored.

source: Il est à espérer que la plupart des gens réaliseront que leur meilleure option à long terme est de travailler ensemble.
reference: Hopefully, most people will realise that their long term best option is to work together with others.
translation: It is hoped that most people will realize that their best long-term option is to work together.

source: Beaucoup rêvent du jour où nous pourrons voyager vers une autre étoile et explorer d'autres mondes. Pour certains, il s'agit de savoir ce qu'il y a ailleurs, d'autres croient que des extraterrestres ou d'autres formes de vie pourraient vivre sur une autre planète.
reference: Many people dream of the day when humans can travel to another star and explore other worlds, some people wonder what's out there some belive that aliens or other life may live on another plant.
translation: Many dream of the day when we can travel to another star and explore other worlds. Some believe that aliens or other forms of life could live on another planet.

source: Toutefois, si cela devait se produire, ce ne serait sûrement pas avant très longtemps. Les étoiles sont si éloignées les unes des autres qu'il y a des milliards de kilomètres entre des étoiles dites voisines.
reference: But, if this ever does happen probably won't happen for a very long time. The stars are so spread out that there are trillions of miles between stars that are "neighbors".
translation: However, if that did happen, it would probably not be before very long. The distances between stars are so great that there are billions of light-years between stars that are called neighbors.

source: Un jour peut-être, vos arrière-petits-enfants se retrouveront sur un monde extra-terrestre, à s'interroger sur leurs lointains ancêtres ?
reference: Maybe one day, your great grandchildren will be standing atop an alien world wondering about their ancient ancestors?
translation: Maybe someday, your grandchildren will be wondering about their distant ancestors.

source: Les animaux sont constitués de nombreuses cellules. Ils mangent toutes sortes de choses et les digèrent naturellement. La plupart des animaux peuvent se déplacer.
reference: Animals are made of many cells. They eat things and digest them inside. Most animals can move.
translation: Animals are made up of many cells. They eat all kinds of things and digest naturally. Most animals can move.

source: Seuls les animaux ont un cerveau (même si tous les animaux n’en ont pas ; les méduses, par exemple, n’ont pas de cerveau).
reference: Only animals have brains (though not even all animals do; jellyfish, for example, do not have brains).
translation: Only animals have brains (even though all animals do not have brains; the medusae, for example, do not have brains).

source: On trouve des animaux partout sur la Terre. Ils creusent le sol, nagent dans les océans et volent dans le ciel.
reference: Animals are found all over the earth. They dig in the ground, swim in the oceans, and fly in the sky.
translation: Animals are everywhere on the earth. They dig the earth, swim in the ocean, and fly in the sky.

source: Une cellule est la plus petite unité structurelle et fonctionnelle d'un organisme vivant.
reference: A cell is the smallest structural and functional unit of a living (things) organism.
translation: A cell is the smallest structural and functional unit of a living organism.

source: Cellule vient du mot latin cella signifiant petite pièce.
reference: Cell comes from the Latin word cella which means small room.
translation: Cellular comes from the Latin word for cell meaning small room.

source: Si vous regardez les êtres vivants sous un microscope, vous verrez qu'ils sont faits de petits carrés ou de boules.
reference: If you look at living things under a microscope, you will see that they are made of small squares or balls.
translation: If you look at living things under a microscope, you will see that they are made of small squares or balls.

source: Robert Hooke, un biologiste anglais, a vu de petits carrés dans du liège avec un microscope.
reference: Robert Hooke, a biologist from England, saw small squares in cork with a microscope.
translation: Robert Hooke, a British biologist, saw small squares in liège with a microscope.

source: Elles ressemblaient à des pièces. Il fut le premier à observer des cellules mortes.
reference: They looked like rooms. He was the first person to observe dead cells
translation: They looked like pieces. He first observed dead cells.

source: Eléments et composants sont capables de passer d'un état à l'autre sans se modifier pour autant.
reference: Elements and compounds can move from one state to another and not change.
translation: Elements and components can change their state without changing their state.

source: L'azote sous forme gazeuse conserve les mêmes propriétés que l'azote liquide. L'état liquide est plus dense, mais les molécules restent identiques.
reference: Nitrogen as a gas still has the same properties as liquid nitrogen. The liquid state is denser but the molecules are still the same.
translation: Nitrogen in gaseous form retains the same properties as nitrogen in liquid form. The liquid state is more dense, but the molecules remain the same.

source: L'eau est un autre exemple. L'eau est composée de deux atomes d'hydrogène et d'un atome d'oxygène.
reference: Water is another example. The compound water is made up of two hydrogen atoms and one oxygen atom.
translation: Water is another example. Water is made up of two hydrogen atoms and one oxygen atom.

source: Il a la même structure moléculaire, qu’il s’agisse d’un gaz, d’un liquide ou d’un solide.
reference: It has the same molecular structure whether it is a gas, liquid, or solid.
translation: It has the same molecular structure, whether it is a gas, liquid or solid.

source: Bien que son état physique puisse varier, sa structure chimique reste constante.
reference: Although its physical state may change, its chemical state remains the same.
translation: While his physical condition may vary, his chemical structure remains the same.

source: Le temps est quelque chose qui nous entoure et qui affecte tout ce que nous faisons, et pourtant il est difficile à comprendre.
reference: Time is something that is all around us, and affects everything we do, yet is difficult to understand.
translation: Time is something that surrounds us and affects everything we do, and yet it is difficult to understand.

source: Le temps a été étudié par des érudits religieux, philosophiques et scientifiques pendant des milliers d'années.
reference: Time has been studied by religious, philosophical, and scientific scholars for thousands of years.
translation: Time has been studied by religious, philosophic and scientific scholars for millennia.

source: Nous vivons le temps comme une série d'événements qui passent du futur au passé en passant par le présent.
reference: We experience time as a series of events passing from the future through the present to the past.
translation: We live the time as a series of events that pass from the future to the past, from the present to the future.

source: Le temps est également un moyen de comparer la durée (longueur) des événements.
reference: Time is also how we compare the duration (length) of events.
translation: Time is also a way to compare the duration (length) of events.

source: Vous pouvez marquer le temps qui passe vous-même en observant la répétition d'un événement cyclique. Un événement cyclique est quelque chose qui se reproduit régulièrement.
reference: You can mark the passing of time yourself by observing the repetition of a cyclical event. A cyclical event is something that happens again and again regularly.
translation: You can mark the time by observing the repetition of a cyclic event. A cyclic event is something that repeats itself regularly.

source: De nos jours, les ordinateurs sont utilisés pour modifier des photos et des vidéos.
reference: Computers today are used to manipulate pictures and videos.
translation: Today, computers are used to edit photos and videos.

source: Les ordinateurs peuvent générer des animations complexes, de plus en plus utilisées à la télévision et au cinéma.
reference: Sophisticated animations can be constructed on computers, and this kind of animation is increasingly being used in television and films.
translation: The computers can generate complex animations, which are increasingly used in television and cinema.

source: On enregistre souvent la musique avec des ordinateurs sophistiqués qui permettent de transformer et mixer des sons ensemble.
reference: Music is often recorded using sophisticated computers to process and mix sounds together.
translation: We often record music with sophisticated computers that can transform and mix sound together.

source: Pendant longtemps au cours des XIXe et XXe siècles, on a cru que les premiers habitants de la Nouvelle-Zélande étaient les Maoris, qui chassaient des oiseaux géants appelés moas.
reference: For a long time during the nineteenth and twentieth centuries, it was believed the first inhabitants of New Zealand were the Maori people, who hunted giant birds called moas.
translation: During the 19th and 20th centuries, people believed that the first inhabitants of New Zealand were the Maoris, who hunted giant birds called moas.

source: La théorie a ensuite établi l'idée que le peuple Maori a migré de Polynésie dans une Grande Flotte et a pris la Nouvelle-Zélande aux Moriori, établissant une société agricole.
reference: The theory then established the idea that the Maori people migrated from Polynesia in a Great Fleet and took New Zealand from the Moriori, establishing an agricultural society.
translation: The theory then established that the Maori people migrated from Polynesia to New Zealand and settled in the Maori, establishing a farming society.

source: Cependant, une nouvelle preuve suggère que les Moriori étaient un groupe de Maoris du continent qui ont migré de la Nouvelle-Zélande vers les îles Chatham, développant leur propre culture distincte et pacifique.
reference: However, new evidence suggests that the Moriori were a group of mainland Maori who migrated from New Zealand to the Chatham Islands, developing their own distinctive, peaceful culture.
translation: However, a new evidence suggests that the Moriori were a Maori group from the continent who migrated to New Zealand from the Chatham Islands, developing their own distinct culture and peaceful lifestyle.

source: Il y avait également une autre tribu sur les îles Chatham : il s'agissait de Maoris qui avaient migré loin de la Nouvelle-Zélande.
reference: There was also another tribe on the Chatham islands these were Maori who migrated away from New Zealand.
translation: There were also other Maoris on the Chatham Islands, who had migrated far away from New Zealand.

source: Ils se sont eux-mêmes appelés les Moriori, et après quelques accrochages, les Moriori ont finalement été éliminés.
reference: They called themselves the Moriori there were a few skirmishes and in the end, the Moriori were wiped out
translation: They themselves called themselves Moriori, and after some fighting, they finally were eliminated.

source: Des personnes impliquées depuis plusieurs décennies nous ont aidés à comprendre nos forces et nos passions tout en évaluant honnêtement nos difficultés et même nos échecs.
reference: Individuals who had been involved for several decades helped us appreciate our strengths and passions while candidly assessing difficulties and even failures.
translation: We have been helping people for decades to understand our strengths and passions, and to evaluate our difficulties and even our failures.

source: En écoutant les individus raconter leur histoire personnelle, familiale et au sein de l'organisation, nous avons pu obtenir des informations précieuses sur le passé et sur certaines des personnalités qui ont influencé positivement ou négativement la culture de l'organisation.
reference: While listening to individuals share their individual, family, and organizational stories, we gained valuable insight into the past and some of the personalities who influenced for good or ill the culture of the organization.
translation: We listened to the individuals tell their personal story, family story and within the organization, we were able to obtain valuable information about the past and some of the individuals who have positively or negatively influenced the culture of the organization.

source: Bien que comprendre l'histoire de quelqu'un ne soit pas synonyme de comprendre sa culture, cela aide les gens à savoir à quel niveau ils se situent dans l'histoire de l'organisation.
reference: While understanding one’s history does not assume understanding of culture, it does at least help people gain a sense of where they fall within the history of the organization.
translation: The translation is not intended to be exhaustive.

source: En évaluant les succès et en prenant conscience des échecs, les individus et l’ensemble des personnes participantes découvrent plus profondément les valeurs, la mission, et les forces directrices de l’organisation.
reference: While assessing the successes and becoming aware of failures, individuals and the whole of the participating persons discover more deeply the values, mission, and driving forces of the organization.
translation: The evaluation of successes and the recognition of failures, individuals and the whole organization, discover more deeply the values, mission, and guiding forces of the organization.

source: En l’occurrence, le fait de se rappeler des exemples précédents de comportement entrepreneurial et des succès qui en ont résulté a aidé les gens à s’ouvrir à de nouveaux changements et a aidé l'église locale à prendre une nouvelle direction.
reference: In this instance, recalling previous instances of entrepreneurial behavior and resulting successes helped people to be open to new changes and new direction for the local church.
translation: In this case, remembering the previous examples of entrepreneurial behavior and the successes it has resulted in helped people to open themselves to new changes and helped the local church to take a new direction.

source: De telles réussites ont réduit les craintes de changement, tout en suscitant des tendances positives vers le changement à venir.
reference: Such success stories lessened the fears of change, while creating positive inclinations toward change in the future.
translation: These successes have reduced the fear of change, while also generating positive trends toward change to come.

source: Les schémas de pensée convergents sont des techniques de résolution de problèmes qui unissent des idées ou des domaines différents pour trouver une solution.
reference: Convergent thinking patterns are problem solving techniques that unite different ideas or fields to find a solution.
translation: The convergent thinking techniques are techniques for solving problems that unite ideas or different fields to find a solution.

source: Cet état d'esprit repose sur la rapidité, la logique et l'exactitude, mais aussi l'identification des faits, la mobilisation de techniques pré-existantes et la recherche d'infos.
reference: The focus of this mindset is speed, logic and accuracy, also identification of facts, reapplying existing techniques, gathering information.
translation: This attitude is based on speed, logic and accuracy, but also on the identification of facts, the use of existing techniques and the search for information.

source: Le facteur primordial de cet état d'esprit : seule une réponse est adaptée. Vous ne pensez qu’à deux options : soit c'est la bonne réponse, soit c'est une mauvaise réponse.
reference: The most important factor of this mindset is: there is only one correct answer. You only think of two answers, namely right or wrong.
translation: The fundamental factor of this attitude: only a single answer is appropriate. You only think of two options: either it's the right answer, or it's a wrong answer.

source: Ce type de pensée est associé à certaines procédures scientifiques ou standard.
reference: This type of thinking is associated with certain science or standard procedures.
translation: This type of thinking is associated with certain scientific or standard procedures.

source: Les personnes ayant ce type de pensées ont une pensée logique, sont capables de mémoriser des modèles, de résoudre des problèmes et de travailler sur des tests scientifiques.
reference: People with this type of thinking have logical thinking, are able to memorize patterns, solve problems and work on scientific tests.
translation: This type of thinking is logical, can memorize models, solve problems, and work on scientific tests.

source: L'homme est de loin l'espèce la plus douée pour lire dans les pensées des autres.
reference: Humans are by far the most talented species in reading the minds of others.
translation: The man is far the most gifted for reading in the minds of others.

source: Ce qui signifie que nous sommes en mesure d'anticiper, et non sans succès, les perceptions, intentions, croyances, savoirs et désirs des autres humains.
reference: That means we are able to successfully predict what other humans perceive, intend, believe, know or desire.
translation: This means that we can predict, and not without success, the perceptions, intentions, beliefs, knowledge and desires of other humans.

source: Parmi ces capacités, c'est la capacité de compréhension des intentions de l'autre qui importe le plus. Elle nous permet de résoudre d’éventuelles ambiguïtés posées par certaines actions physiques.
reference: Among these abilities, understanding the intention of others is crucial. It allows us to resolve possible ambiguities of physical actions.
translation: Among these abilities, the most important is the ability to understand the intentions of the other. This ability helps us to resolve any ambiguity that may arise from physical actions.

source: Si vous voyiez quelqu'un briser une vitre de voiture, par exemple, vous penseriez probablement qu'il essaie de voler la voiture d'un inconnu.
reference: For example, if you were to see someone breaking a car window, you would probably assume he was trying to steal a stranger’s car.
translation: If you saw someone break a window of a car, for example, you might think he is trying to steal the car from an unknown.

source: Il faudrait le juger différemment s'il avait perdu les clés de sa voiture, et si c'était sa propre voiture qu'il essayait de forcer.
reference: He would need to be judged differently if he had lost his car keys and it was his own car that he was trying to break into.
translation: It would be different if he lost the keys to his car, and if it was his own car he tried to force.

source: L’IRM est basée sur un phénomène physique appelé résonance magnétique nucléaire (RMN), découvert dans les années 1930 par Felix Bloch (travaillant à l’université de Stanford) et Edward Purcell (de l’université de Harvard).
reference: MRI is based on a physics phenomenon called nuclear magnetic resonance (NMR), which was discovered in the 1930s by Felix Bloch (working at Stanford University) and Edward Purcell (from Harvard University).
translation: MRI is based on a physical phenomenon called nuclear resonance (NMR), discovered in the 1930s by Felix Bloch (a Stanford student) and Edward Purcell (a Harvard student).

source: Dans cette résonance, le champ magnétique et les ondes radio font que les atomes émettent de minuscules signaux radio.
reference: In this resonance, magnetic field and radio waves cause atoms to give off tiny radio signals.
translation: In this resonance, the magnetic field and radio waves make the atoms emit tiny radio signals.

source: En 1970, Raymond Damadian, docteur en médecine et chercheur en sciences, a découvert les bases permettant d'utiliser l'imagerie par résonance magnétique comme outil de diagnostic médical.
reference: In the year 1970, Raymond Damadian, a medical doctor and research scientist, discovered the basis for using magnetic resonance imaging as a tool for medical diagnosis.
translation: In 1970, Raymond Damadian, a doctor and researcher in medicine, discovered the basis for using magnetic resonance imaging as a diagnostic tool.

source: Quatre ans plus tard, un brevet a été accordé, ce qui était le premier brevet au monde délivré dans le domaine de l'IRM.
reference: Four years later a patent was granted, which was the world's first patent issued in the field of MRI.
translation: Four years later, a patent was granted, which was the first patent granted in the field of MRI.

source: En 1977, le Dr. Damadian a achevé la construction du premier scanner IRM pour tout le corps, qu'il a appelé « l'Indomptable ».
